bobsy-die
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:kick up bobsy-die - to make a fuss; a great fuss; pandemonium
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: -
Pronunciation:
Notes: -->ca1900-1905 W.H.B. Orsman recalled (but vaguely: p.c. 1972) a children's game involving clapping of hands, called <i>Bob's-a-die</i> or <i>Bob's-a-daisy</i>  -->1953 17 M A35 Thames DHS (BOB SA DY) [expressing annoyance] -->1953 17 M A39 Thames DHS (BOBBSY DY) -->1953 16 M A34 Thames DHS (BOBBSY-DYE)
